1. What is the value of y in binary format in the below snippet?
reg [5:0] y;
initial
begin
y= 'Ox2;
end
SOLUTION: y= 'Ox2; This is invalid . So, compilation error occurs.

2. What is the value of the b in the below snippet?
integer b;
initial
begin
b= -‘d12/3;
end
SOLUTION: -4

3. What value is passed across the port b in the below snippet?
module test(output [32:0]b);
real a=14.5;
assign b = a;
endmodule
SOLUTION: assign b = a;
          Let us see LHS and RHS .First RHS is real number (14.5).Now, LHS 'b'  is net/reg(vector).When we assign real to reg/net then fractional part is discarded.
          b = 00000000000000000000000000001110
 
4. Find the value of the variable t at 1ns & 20 ns respectively from the below snippet.
time = t;
initial begin
#10 t= $time;
#20 ;
end
SOLUTION: This code has syntax error in which "time = t;" is invalid 
           If its time t;
          Then the output is 1ns=x(unknown)
                             20ns=10 

5. Write an RTL snippet to initialize all the locations of an array of size:10x8 to 0 at 0ns. Depth= 10, Width = 8bits
SOLUTION:
module array_module;
reg [7:0] my_array [0:9];
initial begin
integer i;
  for (i = 0; i < 10; i = i + 1) begin
       my_array[i] = 8'b0;
  end
end
endmodule

6. What will be the value of the parameter constant for the instance DUT in the top module from the below snippet?
module test;
parameter WIDTH=8;
endmodule
module top;
test #(16) OUT ( ) ;
endmodule
SOLUTION:  The value of parameter is 16

7. What is the bug in the following snippet?
module test;
parameter WIDTH=8;
endmodule
module top;
test OUT ( ) ;
initial
defparam OUT.WIDTH=10;
endmodule
SOLUTION:  Bug-'defparam' cannot be used inside an 'initial' block; it must be used outside procedural blocks.

8. What will be displayed in the console mode for the below snippet?
reg[13*8:1]s;
initial
begin
s = "hello world";
$display("Value of s= %s",s[104:65]);
end
SOLUTION: Value of s= hello [Because in ASCII 1char=8bit.]

